The Hamburg Dependency Treebank
===============================

This archive contains the Hamburg Dependency Treebank 1.0.1, converted
to the CoNLL-X format.  The HDT consists of 261.821 sentences
annotated with dependency structure.

Heise Zeitschriften Verlag kindly allowed us to distribute the
underlying articles for scientific/academic use. The
annotations themselves are distributed under a Creative Commons
Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 International License[0].

The HDT is described in detail in [1]. If you use the HDT, please cite
that paper. If you want to contact the creators of the HDT, please
send an email to hdt@informatik.uni-hamburg.de

The persistent Identifier of the HDT is:
http://hdl.handle.net/11022/0000-0000-7FC7-2
(There you can also find the data in the original format)


Annotation
----------

All sentences are annotated according to [2].
The treebank is split into three parts:

  A) automatically parsed, manually revised & checked for consistency
     with DECCA (101.999 sentences)
  B) automatically parsed & manually revised (104.795 sentences)
  C) automatically parsed only (55.027 sentences)


Please consult the archive containing the original cda files for the
mapping from sentences to the corresponding articles, their authors
and the publication date.

Annotation Remarks
------------------

The "Lemma" field is filled with the "base" attribute from the
original annotation, if available.  Otherwise, the original word has
been inserted.



